<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-08-02T02:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-08-02T02:34:00-05:00" n="612" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/3150: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-02T16:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">August 2,
                                        1923—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 2—1:15
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>On August 1 General Chang Huan-hsiang attempted to take over land
                            department of Chinese Eastern Railway but met with opposition and
                            protest on the part of railway officials and representative of
                            Russo-Asiatic Bank. Chinese officials now apparently weakening in their
                            aggressive attitude and endeavoring to find satisfactory retreat from
                            difficulties within which they involved themselves. Legation has been
                            notified.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>